Download libtorrent from:
https://code.google.com/p/libtorrent/downloads/list 

extract libtorrent werever you like, for example in /home/user/libtorrent/

install boost:
sudo apt-get install libboost-all-dev

go to libtorrent folder:
cd /home/user/libtorrent/

run config:
./configure --disable-debug

build libtorrent:
make

optional: run tests:
make check


--------------------------
adapt user-config.jam
set paths to arm-linux-androideabi-ar and arm-linux-androideabi-g++ correct (in both: "using gcc : androidR8e" and "using gcc : androidR8b") by referring to the Android NDK root as so:
$(AndroidNDKRoot)/toolchains/arm-linux-androideabi-4.6/prebuilt/linux-x86/bin/arm-linux-androideabi-g++
$(AndroidNDKRoot)/toolchains/arm-linux-androideabi-4.6/prebuilt/linux-x86/bin/arm-linux-androideabi-ar


for building libtorrent to android:

sudo b2 --user-config=/home/jaap/git/Boost-for-Android/boost_1_53_0/tools/build/v2/user-config.jam toolset=gcc-androidR8e boost=source link=static runtime-link=static target-os=linux --stagedir=android release

